    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single below-requirement factor (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because ASTM F1717 is the regulatory standard configuration and represents the worst-case loading scenario for this device class. Overall model credibility is sufficient to support the regulatory submission claim for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
